Heat a saucepan over a medium heat. Add the chorizo, onion and garlic and fry for 3-4 minutes, until the chorizo is golden brown all over.Add the remaining stew ingredients, except for the fresh herbs. Bring to the boil, then simmer for 10-12 minutes.Add the herbs and stir well.For the croutons, heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. When hot, add the puff pastry triangles and fry for 4-5 minutes, turning once, until crisp and golden all over.